    "summary": "\"The Way (道, dao)\" — romanized Dao available via gloss",
    "content": "**\"The Way (道, dao)\"** in the glossed block quote. \n\nThe gloss gives the reader the romanization anyway, so they have \"Dao\" available. But \"the Way\" is the English rendering — it is what appears in running text thereafter when quoting or referencing Laozi. If the author then uses 道 in their own constructivist analysis, that is where the shift to \"Dao\" (romanized) can happen, paralleling the virtue → character shift for 德."
  }
}
